Marketing Brief -- Adolph Coors Co.:
   Unit's Keystone Dry Beer
   Set for National Distribution
Dry beer, which was developed by Japan's Asahi Brewing, is
advertised as being less sweet and having less of an
aftertaste than other beers.
   The dry beer category has about 2.2% of the nation's beer
market. The first U.S.produced dry beer was Michelob Dry, and
the nation's largest-selling dry beer is Bud Dry, both brewed
by Anheuser.